Example03
=========
  Geant4 ExampleN03 adapted to Virtual Monte Carlo.

  Demonstrates:
    Geometry - divided volume (Gsdvn)
    Definition of sensitive volumes
    Physics - hadronics processes off
    Particles cuts 
      - G4 cut in range: 1mm
        G3 cuts set to correspond to 1mm cut in range
    Primary generator with randomized position (optional)
      defined number of electrons with moving position and fixed direction
    Calorimetry hits
    Storing hits, particles stack in Root file
    Drawing geometry (G3, G3+TGeo, G4) + trajectories (G3+TGeo and G4)
    Verbosity
    User defined physics list (G4)

  See also description of in 
    geant4/examples/novice/N03/README

Compilation:
============
  With G4:
  An extra library with user defined physics list has to be build:
  
  cd E03/geant4
  gmake

  Use of user own defined physics list is demonstrated on
  the LHEP_BERT hadronics physics list provided in Geant4;
  to build its libraries:

  cd $G4INSTALL/physics_lists/hadronic/Packaging
  gmake
  cd $G4INSTALL/physics_lists/hadronic/LHEP_BERT
  gmake
     

Macros:
=======

  For running example with G3:
  
  run_g3.C        - macro for running example 
  g3Config.C      - configuration macro for G3 with native geometry (default)
  g3tgeoConfig.C  - configuration macro for G3 with TGeo geometry

  For running example with G4:
  
  run_g4.C     - macro for running example 
  g4Config.C   - configuration macro
  g4Config2.C  - configuration macro with user defined physics list (LHEP_BERT)
  g4config.in  - Geant4 configuration macro (called from g4Config.C)
  g4vis.in     - Geant4 macro for visualization settings (called from set_vis.C) 

  Common macros (called by run_g3.C/run_g4.C):
  
  test1.C   - calorimetry (default)
  test2.C   - verbosity
  set_vis.C - setting visualization

To run example 
===============
  The first line shows how to run the first test macro (test1.C),
  the second line to run the second test macro (test2.C):
  
  With G3:
  root[0] .x run_g3.C      
  root[0] .x run_g3.C("g3Config.C", "test2.C")      
  
  With G3 + TGeo:
  root[0] .x run_g3.C("g3tgeoConfig.C");  
  root[0] .x run_g3.C("g3tgeoConfig.C", "test2.C")      
  
  With G4:
  root[0] .x run_g4.C  
  root[0] .x run_g4.C("g4Config.C", "test2.C")

  With G4 with user defined physics list:
  root[0] .x run_g4.C("g4Config2.C"); 
  root[0] .x run_g4.C("g4Config2.C", "test2.C")
